properties.description: Posted by Jenniferrt

properties.name: Alcatraz
properties.description: Posted by JenniferrtI got to go to Alcareaz and do the walk through story explaining the story of Alcatraz and why it was shut down. This was one of my favorite parts about San Francisco.

properties.name: Beautiful state
properties.description: Posted by JenniferrtI was in Rhode Island during Autumn and the trees were absolutly beautiful. We were just driving through, but it was beautiful enough to remember.

properties.name: DC
properties.description: Posted by JenniferrtWashington DCWhen I went I visited the typical toursit sites. There was so much to see and I was pretty young so I don\'t really remember specifics.

properties.name: Great Grandma
properties.description: Posted by JenniferrtAt the time my great grandma lived in Birmingham and we went to visit her. She spoiled us so much and we had tons of fun with her. This was one of the few times I go to see her.

properties.name: Historic Train Site
properties.description: Posted by JenniferrtI visited the historic Rocky Mt. Train Site.

properties.name: History Day
properties.description: Posted by JenniferrtSan Francisco CaliforniaI have actually been to San francisco a few times. My first time was when I was in the 8th grade. I was participating in a program know as History Day and our state finals were held in San Francisco. My second time was when i was a freshman. I got to visit Alcatraz and experiece the city in a different way.

properties.name: Home
properties.description: Posted by JenniferrtI was born here. I moved to Tennesse for 8 years then moved back and have been here ever since. I went to high school in Fontana, at Kaiser High School.

properties.name: Hurricane
properties.description: Posted by JenniferrtI had the opportunity to visit the gulf region. This was one of the regions devastated by Hurricane Katrina.

properties.name: Junior Year trip
properties.description: Posted by JenniferrtSan Diego CaliforniaWhen I was a junior in high school I went on a week long trip to San Diego. To a lot of people a week is very short, but I had so much fun. I got to perform at a musical festivl and just go out on my own and explore. It was my first time being to San Diego since I was 9 so it was exciting.

properties.name: My 2nd home
properties.description: Posted by JenniferrtWhen I was 10 months old i moved to crossville Tennessee. I lived ther until I was 8 years old. Then we moved right back to Fontana. I started school in Tennessee. My school went K-8. It as an indoor school and all white. There was little diversity in the city I lived in.

properties.name: Myrtle Beach
properties.description: Posted by Jenniferrt  we went and visited the beach and it is known for the white sandy beaches and it was beautiful. It was another trip with my dad so it made it even more special.

properties.name: New Orleans
properties.description: Posted by JenniferrtLouisiana is very unique. There is a very diferent culture and it is very intersting. Not to mention the food is great. Now this area is forever cgangerd because of Hurricane Katrina.

properties.name: Snow...
properties.description: Posted by JenniferrtMy mom\'s best friend lives here, and we went when I was 10 for Thanksgiving. It was snowing, which was very weird for the time of year. I got to meet a lot of my mom\'s old friends and people that I knew about but had never had the chance to meet.

properties.name: Snowed in
properties.description: Posted by JenniferrtWe were traveling through Maine and there was a blizzard. We got stuck in a store prking lot for 2 days because we were snowed in.

properties.name: Tornado
properties.description: Posted by JenniferrtWhen I lived in Tennessee I took gymnastics in Nashville at an olymipc training vcenter. One day my mom had a weird feeling that I shouldn\'t go and that night there were about 12 tornadoes that touched down in the area. We watched the tornado go right by our hous and luckuily not cause our house any damage.

properties.name: USC game
properties.description: Posted by JenniferrtMy mom took my sister and I to meet my grandpa and we went to the USC vs. Oklahoma college game. After he game we went to dinner and my grandpa bought me orange gum and I remember it being gross...

properties.name: What an Experience...
properties.description: Posted by JenniferrtWhen I was younger my dad was a distance truck driver and we got to go everywhere with him. My only memory of Boston is that the people were hard to understand and that they weren\'t very polite. But I was so excited to get to travel. This is one of the first places I remember traveling to.

properties.name: another road trip
properties.description: Posted by Jenniferrt

properties.name: road trip
properties.description: Posted by JenniferrtThis was another trip taken with my dad. I was really young so I don\'t remember specfics, but I do remember being in awe of the buildings. I lived in the country so to go to a place like New York was quite a shock.

properties.name: water issues
properties.description: Posted by JenniferrtMy family and I were driving through Arizona, I can\'t remember exactly where, but we coulodnt drink the water. To me this was weird because I was used to being able to go anywhere and just turn on a faucet and get "clean" water. It was so hot and we had to wait until we got to a gracery store to buy bottle water.
